The paper proposes a conditional GAN approach for multiview learning problems where observations have missing views. This problem is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), information retrieval (cs.IR), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Given that the paper focuses on learning missing views and multiview classification, it is most likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. However, it also involves natural language processing and information retrieval tasks, which make cs.CL and cs.IR likely sub-categories as well. The use of GANs and conditional generation also suggests a possible connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
